// @test regression/INV046-unclosed-bracket
// @description A `[` still open at EOF gets TV's CE10156 'Syntax error at input "["' anchored at the bracket itself (probed: `arr = [1, 2, 3` unclosed errors at the `[`, 8:7). The lexer reports the earliest unclosed opener; the parser's 'Expected "]"' cascade lands later, past TV's stop. See INV046.
// @expects parse: fail
// @expects error: line=3, column=7, message=/Syntax error at input .\[./

//@version=6
indicator("INV046 unclosed bracket")
arr = [1, 2, 3

plot(close)
